Objective :

Legion Zone is the game performance and equipment management center, the pre-installed standard software of the Rescuer equipment.

This case is an LZ hardware related basic function check, focusing on all hardware related test content.
Release notes :

Section : Basic inspection (30) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Note: The current version will upgrade the preinstalled version to the official website version. If you are prompted to update during the test, please do not update. During the test, ensure that the test version is correct
Ensure that the software version is the test version
1.Check the legion zone‘设置中心’
Page display is complete without garbled code, interface error and leakage, key missing, key can not be clicked and other problems
1.1 Click on "设置中心" -"启动设置" will be checked by default
Legion Zone starts from the system tray at boot time
 
Section : Performance control (180) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
1. After the Legion Zone is started for the first time, it remains on the "首页" page by default
Page display is complete without garbled code, interface error and leakage, key missing, key can not be clicked and other problems
2. Check the Thermal Mode
Displa‘安静’, ‘均衡’, ‘野兽’, ‘默认自定义模式’ Entering the‘首页’page for the first time, the thermal mode is in balance mode
3. Thermal mode color theme check
Quiet Mode (Blue)/Balanced Mode (White)/Performance Mode (Red)/Custom Mode (Purple)
3.1 Linkage check between performance mode and power lamp effect (if there is no power RGB color lights on the test machine, it does not need to be performed)
Power light and performance mode color theme: Quiet mode (blue)/Balance Mode (white)/Performance Mode (red)/Custom Mode (purple)
4. Check the Thermal mode parameter display
4.1 Checking the CPU Frequency And utilization rate
CPU frequency changes every 2S. Start the task Manager and check the CPU Speed without significant error
4.2 Checking the GPU Frequency And utilization rate
GPU frequency changes every 2S. Enable Gpu-z →Sensors→GPU Clock without major error There is a possibility that the Gpu z version cannot recognize the new GPU, and other tools such （as HWinfo64） can be used for read testing.
4.3 Checking the CPU Temperature
Start HWINF Tool→Sensors to check that the CPU temperature is consistent with the CPU temperature displayed in Legion Zone
4.4 Checking the GPU Temperature
Start HWINF Tool→Sensors to check that the GPU temperature is consistent with the GPU temperature displayed in Legion Zone
4.5 Checking the CPU Usage
The CPU usage is consistent with that of the task manager
4.6 Checking the GPU Usage
The GPU usage is consistent with that of the task manager
4.7 Checking the DRAM Frequency
Open Task Manager → Performance → Memory and check that the memory rate is consistent with the DRAM value in Legion Zone interface
4.8 Check the display of DRAM usage
Start Task Manager → Performance → Memory and check that the memory usage is the same as that in Legion Zone
4.9 Checking the Fan Speed
The fan speed is correct (Obtain the Thermal RD check tool from thermal RD. Different types of check tools are different.)
4.10 Checking the CPU/GPU One-Click Overfrequency Status
One-click overclocking exists only in the Balanced/Performance mode. If one-click overclocking is not supported, related keys are not displayed. If overclocking is not enabled in the BIOS, related keys are not displayed in the software PS: If the project has requirements on the default overclocking state, the project requirements shall prevail. If the project has no specific requirements, the overclocking state shall be turned off by default
5.Switch thermal mode on the '性能管控' page and view the radar image display
The radar image displayed in each thermal mode is normal with no error messages Note：Extreme mode and custom mode are two different modes, and the radar image display is also inconsistent
5.1 Turn on the CPU/GPU oc switch in Balance/performance mode. Please confirm with the project whether it supports CPU/GPU OC
The CPU and GPU vertices in the radar map change accordingly
6. Resolution test
6.1 Drag the four side borders or four corner positions of the main window of the Legion zone to zoom in or out of the Legion zone
The Legion zone page displays normally, with no error messages or garbled characters
6.2.1Click the full screen button in the upper right corner,
The Legion zone page displays normally, with no error messages or garbled characters，
 
Section : Home page-Utility Card (120) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Note: Due to inconsistent display refresh rates, the display of utility cards in the legion area may also be different. Please test the practical card function displayed on the machine. If it is not supported, please skip it.
Display Mode Practical Card
Click the switch button in the upper right corner of the display mode utility card,
You can switch between intelligent display mode and standalone direct connection. Synchronize with the display mode in 'Utility'. Pop up a prompt for '重启后生效'

Display mode successfully switched

The default state is correct
Click the on/off button to switch the status of the logo light
Check if the back logo lights are on or off synchronously Click on "Light Effect Adjustment" - the back display page will synchronize the light effect logo light with the homepage status
Touchpad Practical Card

The default state is correct

The switch can be switched normally, and the touchpad function is synchronized according to the switch function
Set the keyboard top row fuction to special fuction, use the shortcut F10 to disable touchpad, restart the legion zone, and check if the Touchpad lock is synchronized and closed
Touchpad lock function synced off
Turn on/off the Touchpad lock function, perform S3/S4/S5/WB operations, and check if the touchpad is functioning properly
Touchpad is normal and can be used when turned on, but cannot be used when turned off
Charging Mode Practical Card
Please confirm with the project the default state of the charging mode
The default state is correct
Click the switch button in the upper right corner of the charging mode
The charging mode can be switched normally. Need to be consistent with the charging mode in the toolbox
Download the attachment idea GUI tool, start the tool, and complete the following tests Tool download Find GUI Tool → Power → Rapid Charge Check if the machine supports functions and if they are enabled
The Rapid charge status is: The ON machine is actually in fast charge mode Status: OFF The machine is actually in normal mode
OverDrive Practical Card
Please confirm with the project the default state of the OD
The default state is correct
Click the switch button in the upper right corner
Can be switched normally Synchronize with Toolbox Screen Settings OD Status
Using the WMI interface tool to check the actual status of OD
Download the attachment OD inspection tool, File Code Language → Set as follows: 1. namespace: root WMI 2. Classes with methods: LENOVO_ GAMEZONE_ DATA 3. Methods: GetODStatus → Select 'InstanceNamexxxxxxxxxxx' → Execute Code Check the inverse data: If 0, it is' OFF ' If it is 1, it is' ON '
Intelligent Optimization of Games Practical Card
Click to switch the switch in the upper right corner
The button can be turned on or off normally
Keyboard Light Brightness Practical Card
Please confirm with the project the default state of the Keyboard ligt brightness
The default state is correct
Slide the progress bar left and right
The lighting effect synchronously brightens or darkens Synchronize with the brightness bar on the lighting adjustment page
Use the fn+↑/fn+↓ buttons to adjust keyboard brightness
The practical card for keyboard brightness will also refresh with the refresh
Note: The cards displayed on the right side of the Legion Zone are "上次游玩游戏", "Steam加速", and "运营位". This card displays the need to connect to the network and log in to a Lenovo account.
View and click on the ‘运营位’ Card
The page displays normally without garbled characters, and the buttons can be opened normally. The card can be redirected to other pages normally
Note: The 'Last Run Game' card is displayed based on the first game displayed on my game page
Click to switch between different card states Do Sleep/Hibernate/Cold boot/Warm boot operations.Restart Legion Zone to check if the function has been saved.
The card status can be successfully saved After clicking the switch button, the "Display Mode Utility Card" will perform reboot operations, and the graphics card mode will switch to different modes.
 
Section : PD pop-up check (30) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
PS: The original power supply and the next gear power supply of the original power supply are both adaptive power supplies, such as 300W compatible with 230W, 230W compatible with 170W Under non compatible power supply, the Legion Zone will be considered as the system in DC state
Connect the non original power adapter (original power supply and the next gear is the power supply) and check the APP pop-up prompt
The correct pop-up prompt on the APP indicates the information of connecting to the power supply
Switch to Beast Mode/Custom Mode by Accessing a Non Adaptive Charger
Unable to switch to Beast/Custom mode, prompt 'Please insert the original power adapter to switch to Beast/Custom mode'
Connect to non adaptive charger to enable CPU/GPU one click overclocking
Unable to enable CPU/GPU one click overclocking function, relevant options dimmed
